HEADWORD: Exinanition
<hw>Ex*in`a*ni"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exinanitio</ets>.]</ety> <def>An emptying; an enfeebling;
exhaustion; humiliation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fastings to the <qex>exinanition</qex> of spirits.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

